Mood Selection and Suggestions:

Users can select their current mood from a list of moods. Based on the selection, the app shows a list of suggested activities that match the mood.
Adding Tasks to the Planner:

The app allows users to add suggested tasks to their planner. The tasks are stored in a list, and a snack bar confirms the addition of each task.
Viewing the Planner:

Users can tap on the calendar icon in the top-right corner to view all tasks added to their planner. This opens a new screen (PlannerScreen) displaying a list of all the tasks added.
PlannerScreen:

This screen shows the list of all tasks the user has added to their planner. If no tasks have been added, it displays a message indicating that the planner is empty.
